{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":671,"text":"Hi. So, this chap here,"},{"time":3456,"text":"he thinks he can tell you the future."},{"time":5718,"text":"His name is Nostradamus, although here the Sun have"},{"time":7697,"text":"made him look a little bit like Sean Connery. (Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":11367,"text":"And like most of you, I suspect, I don't really believe"},{"time":14270,"text":"that people can see into the future."},{"time":15378,"text":"I don't believe in precognition, and every now and then,"},{"time":18082,"text":"you hear that somebody has been able to predict something that happened in the future,"},{"time":21264,"text":"and that's probably because it was a fluke, and we only"},{"time":24323,"text":"hear about the flukes and about the freaks."},{"time":26938,"text":"We don't hear about all the times that people got stuff wrong."},{"time":31017,"text":"Now we expect that to happen with silly stories"},{"time":33177,"text":"about precognition, but the problem is,"},{"time":36316,"text":"we have exactly the same problem in academia"},{"time":39660,"text":"and in medicine, and in this environment, it costs lives."}]},{"cues":[{"time":44161,"text":"So firstly, thinking just about precognition, as it turns out,"},{"time":47526,"text":"just last year a researcher called Daryl Bem conducted"},{"time":50055,"text":"a piece of research where he found evidence"},{"time":51891,"text":"of precognitive powers in undergraduate students,"},{"time":55549,"text":"and this was published in a peer-reviewed academic journal"},{"time":58123,"text":"and most of the people who read this just said, \"Okay, well,"},{"time":60404,"text":"fair enough, but I think that's a fluke, that's a freak, because I know"},{"time":62585,"text":"that if I did a study where I found no evidence"},{"time":65419,"text":"that undergraduate students had precognitive powers,"},{"time":67931,"text":"it probably wouldn't get published in a journal."},{"time":71483,"text":"And in fact, we know that that's true, because"},{"time":74338,"text":"several different groups of research scientists tried"},{"time":76867,"text":"to replicate the findings of this precognition study,"},{"time":80387,"text":"and when they submitted it to the exact same journal,"},{"time":83022,"text":"the journal said, \"No, we're not interested in publishing"},{"time":86174,"text":"replication. We're not interested in your negative data.\""},{"time":90699,"text":"So this is already evidence of how, in the academic"},{"time":93453,"text":"literature, we will see a biased sample of the true picture"},{"time":98323,"text":"of all of the scientific studies that have been conducted."}]},{"cues":[{"time":101790,"text":"But it doesn't just happen in the dry academic field of psychology."},{"time":106219,"text":"It also happens in, for example, cancer research."},{"time":110586,"text":"So in March, 2012, just one month ago, some researchers"},{"time":114663,"text":"reported in the journal Nature how they had tried"},{"time":117559,"text":"to replicate 53 different basic science studies looking at"},{"time":121405,"text":"potential treatment targets in cancer,"},{"time":124960,"text":"and out of those 53 studies, they were only able"},{"time":127598,"text":"to successfully replicate six."},{"time":130674,"text":"Forty-seven out of those 53 were unreplicable."},{"time":135007,"text":"And they say in their discussion that this is very likely"},{"time":138920,"text":"because freaks get published."},{"time":141559,"text":"People will do lots and lots and lots of different studies,"},{"time":143655,"text":"and the occasions when it works they will publish,"},{"time":145775,"text":"and the ones where it doesn't work they won't."},{"time":147454,"text":"And their first recommendation of how to fix this problem,"},{"time":151395,"text":"because it is a problem, because it sends us all down blind alleys,"},{"time":154684,"text":"their first recommendation of how to fix this problem"},{"time":156390,"text":"is to make it easier to publish negative results in science,"},{"time":159783,"text":"and to change the incentives so that scientists are"},{"time":162690,"text":"encouraged to post more of their negative results in public."}]},{"cues":[{"time":167042,"text":"But it doesn't just happen in the very dry world"},{"time":170894,"text":"of preclinical basic science cancer research."},{"time":174745,"text":"It also happens in the very real, flesh and blood"},{"time":178402,"text":"of academic medicine. So in 1980,"},{"time":181993,"text":"some researchers did a study on a drug called lorcainide,"},{"time":185001,"text":"and this was an anti-arrhythmic drug,"},{"time":187332,"text":"a drug that suppresses abnormal heart rhythms,"},{"time":189598,"text":"and the idea was, after people have had a heart attack,"},{"time":191826,"text":"they're quite likely to have abnormal heart rhythms,"},{"time":193363,"text":"so if we give them a drug that suppresses abnormal heart"},{"time":195740,"text":"rhythms, this will increase the chances of them surviving."},{"time":199453,"text":"Early on its development, they did a very small trial,"},{"time":202461,"text":"just under a hundred patients."},{"time":204105,"text":"Fifty patients got lorcainide, and of those patients, 10 died."},{"time":207757,"text":"Another 50 patients got a dummy placebo sugar pill"},{"time":210800,"text":"with no active ingredient, and only one of them died."},{"time":213758,"text":"So they rightly regarded this drug as a failure,"},{"time":216407,"text":"and its commercial development was stopped, and because"},{"time":219276,"text":"its commercial development was stopped, this trial was never published."}]},{"cues":[{"time":223624,"text":"Unfortunately, over the course of the next five, 10 years,"},{"time":229021,"text":"other companies had the same idea about drugs that would"},{"time":232846,"text":"prevent arrhythmias in people who have had heart attacks."},{"time":235438,"text":"These drugs were brought to market. They were prescribed"},{"time":237158,"text":"very widely because heart attacks are a very common thing,"},{"time":240570,"text":"and it took so long for us to find out that these drugs"},{"time":244413,"text":"also caused an increased rate of death"},{"time":247324,"text":"that before we detected that safety signal,"},{"time":250071,"text":"over 100,000 people died unnecessarily in America"},{"time":256122,"text":"from the prescription of anti-arrhythmic drugs."}]},{"cues":[{"time":259573,"text":"Now actually, in 1993,"},{"time":263171,"text":"the researchers who did that 1980 study, that early study,"},{"time":266731,"text":"published a mea culpa, an apology to the scientific community,"},{"time":270572,"text":"in which they said, \"When we carried out our study in 1980,"},{"time":273697,"text":"we thought that the increased death rate that occurred"},{"time":275633,"text":"in the lorcainide group was an effect of chance.\""},{"time":278991,"text":"The development of lorcainide was abandoned for commercial reasons,"},{"time":281023,"text":"and this study was never published;"},{"time":282661,"text":"it's now a good example of publication bias."},{"time":285047,"text":"That's the technical term for the phenomenon where"},{"time":286938,"text":"unflattering data gets lost, gets unpublished, is left"},{"time":291176,"text":"missing in action, and they say the results described here"},{"time":294547,"text":"\"might have provided an early warning of trouble ahead.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":299355,"text":"Now these are stories from basic science."},{"time":302568,"text":"These are stories from 20, 30 years ago."},{"time":307355,"text":"The academic publishing environment is very different now."},{"time":310502,"text":"There are academic journals like \"Trials,\" the open access journal,"},{"time":314497,"text":"which will publish any trial conducted in humans"},{"time":317152,"text":"regardless of whether it has a positive or a negative result."},{"time":320455,"text":"But this problem of negative results that go missing in action"},{"time":324424,"text":"is still very prevalent. In fact it's so prevalent"},{"time":327983,"text":"that it cuts to the core of evidence-based medicine."},{"time":333834,"text":"So this is a drug called reboxetine, and this is a drug"},{"time":336849,"text":"that I myself have prescribed. It's an antidepressant."},{"time":339384,"text":"And I'm a very nerdy doctor, so I read all of the studies"},{"time":341920,"text":"that I could on this drug. I read the one study that was published"},{"time":344972,"text":"that showed that reboxetine was better than placebo,"},{"time":347919,"text":"and I read the other three studies that were published"},{"time":349783,"text":"that showed that reboxetine was just as good as any other antidepressant,"},{"time":353354,"text":"and because this patient hadn't done well on those other antidepressants,"},{"time":355541,"text":"I thought, well, reboxetine is just as good. It's one to try."},{"time":358007,"text":"But it turned out that I was misled. In fact,"},{"time":361399,"text":"seven trials were conducted comparing reboxetine"},{"time":363848,"text":"against a dummy placebo sugar pill. One of them"},{"time":366560,"text":"was positive and that was published, but six of them"},{"time":368872,"text":"were negative and they were left unpublished."},{"time":372920,"text":"Three trials were published comparing reboxetine"},{"time":374659,"text":"against other antidepressants in which reboxetine"},{"time":376885,"text":"was just as good, and they were published,"},{"time":378678,"text":"but three times as many patients' worth of data was collected"},{"time":383067,"text":"which showed that reboxetine was worse than"},{"time":384938,"text":"those other treatments, and those trials were not published."},{"time":389639,"text":"I felt misled."}]},{"cues":[{"time":393398,"text":"Now you might say, well, that's an extremely unusual example,"},{"time":395528,"text":"and I wouldn't want to be guilty of the same kind of"},{"time":397536,"text":"cherry-picking and selective referencing"},{"time":400517,"text":"that I'm accusing other people of."},{"time":402308,"text":"But it turns out that this phenomenon of publication bias"},{"time":404192,"text":"has actually been very, very well studied."},{"time":406319,"text":"So here is one example of how you approach it."},{"time":408537,"text":"The classic model is, you get a bunch of studies where"},{"time":410977,"text":"you know that they've been conducted and completed,"},{"time":413162,"text":"and then you go and see if they've been published anywhere"},{"time":415483,"text":"in the academic literature. So this took all of the trials"},{"time":418346,"text":"that had ever been conducted on antidepressants"},{"time":420500,"text":"that were approved over a 15-year period by the FDA."},{"time":424142,"text":"They took all of the trials which were submitted to the FDA as part of the approval package."},{"time":427898,"text":"So that's not all of the trials that were ever conducted on these drugs,"},{"time":431098,"text":"because we can never know if we have those,"},{"time":433196,"text":"but it is the ones that were conducted in order to get the marketing authorization."},{"time":436690,"text":"And then they went to see if these trials had been published"},{"time":439039,"text":"in the peer-reviewed academic literature. And this is what they found."},{"time":441611,"text":"It was pretty much a 50-50 split. Half of these trials"},{"time":444780,"text":"were positive, half of them were negative, in reality."},{"time":448377,"text":"But when they went to look for these trials in the peer-reviewed academic literature,"},{"time":453118,"text":"what they found was a very different picture."},{"time":455352,"text":"Only three of the negative trials were published,"},{"time":459724,"text":"but all but one of the positive trials were published."},{"time":464366,"text":"Now if we just flick back and forth between those two,"},{"time":468127,"text":"you can see what a staggering difference there was"},{"time":470721,"text":"between reality and what doctors, patients,"},{"time":474171,"text":"commissioners of health services, and academics"},{"time":476793,"text":"were able to see in the peer-reviewed academic literature."},{"time":480074,"text":"We were misled, and this is a systematic flaw"},{"time":484528,"text":"in the core of medicine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":487858,"text":"In fact, there have been so many studies conducted on"},{"time":490521,"text":"publication bias now, over a hundred, that they've been"},{"time":493905,"text":"collected in a systematic review, published in 2010,"},{"time":497099,"text":"that took every single study on publication bias"},{"time":499865,"text":"that they could find."},{"time":501164,"text":"Publication bias affects every field of medicine."},{"time":504016,"text":"About half of all trials, on average, go missing in action,"},{"time":508329,"text":"and we know that positive findings are around twice as likely"},{"time":511387,"text":"to be published as negative findings."}]},{"cues":[{"time":514441,"text":"This is a cancer at the core of evidence-based medicine."},{"time":518502,"text":"If I flipped a coin 100 times but then"},{"time":522373,"text":"withheld the results from you from half of those tosses,"},{"time":525632,"text":"I could make it look as if I had a coin that always came up heads."},{"time":529032,"text":"But that wouldn't mean that I had a two-headed coin."},{"time":530853,"text":"That would mean that I was a chancer"},{"time":532565,"text":"and you were an idiot for letting me get away with it. (Laughter)"},{"time":535679,"text":"But this is exactly what we blindly tolerate"},{"time":539316,"text":"in the whole of evidence-based medicine."},{"time":543105,"text":"And to me, this is research misconduct."},{"time":547537,"text":"If I conducted one study and I withheld"},{"time":550280,"text":"half of the data points from that one study,"},{"time":553280,"text":"you would rightly accuse me, essentially, of research fraud."},{"time":557987,"text":"And yet, for some reason, if somebody conducts"},{"time":560770,"text":"10 studies but only publishes the five that give the result that they want,"},{"time":565328,"text":"we don't consider that to be research misconduct."},{"time":568116,"text":"And when that responsibility is diffused between"},{"time":570683,"text":"a whole network of researchers, academics,"},{"time":573844,"text":"industry sponsors, journal editors, for some reason"},{"time":577372,"text":"we find it more acceptable,"},{"time":578825,"text":"but the effect on patients is damning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":582500,"text":"And this is happening right now, today."},{"time":587518,"text":"This is a drug called Tamiflu. Tamiflu is a drug"},{"time":590229,"text":"which governments around the world have spent billions"},{"time":592825,"text":"and billions of dollars on stockpiling,"},{"time":595397,"text":"and we've stockpiled Tamiflu in panic,"},{"time":598545,"text":"in the belief that it will reduce the rate of complications of influenza."},{"time":602494,"text":"Complications is a medical euphemism for pneumonia"},{"time":605178,"text":"and death. (Laughter)"},{"time":609992,"text":"Now when the Cochrane systematic reviewers"},{"time":613200,"text":"were trying to collect together all of the data from all"},{"time":615725,"text":"of the trials that had ever been conducted on whether Tamiflu actually did this or not,"},{"time":619373,"text":"they found that several of those trials were unpublished."},{"time":622324,"text":"The results were unavailable to them."},{"time":624166,"text":"And when they started obtaining the writeups of those trials through various different means,"},{"time":628130,"text":"through Freedom of Information Act requests, through"},{"time":629812,"text":"harassing various different organizations, what they found was inconsistent."},{"time":634621,"text":"And when they tried to get a hold of the clinical study reports,"},{"time":637087,"text":"the 10,000-page long documents that have"},{"time":640133,"text":"the best possible rendition of the information,"},{"time":643733,"text":"they were told they weren't allowed to have them."},{"time":646621,"text":"And if you want to read the full correspondence"},{"time":649304,"text":"and the excuses and the explanations given by the drug company,"},{"time":652594,"text":"you can see that written up in this week's edition"},{"time":655311,"text":"of PLOS Medicine."}]},{"cues":[{"time":659678,"text":"And the most staggering thing of all of this, to me,"},{"time":663537,"text":"is that not only is this a problem, not only do we recognize"},{"time":666836,"text":"that this is a problem, but we've had to suffer fake fixes."},{"time":671031,"text":"We've had people pretend that this is a problem that's been fixed."},{"time":674089,"text":"First of all, we had trials registers, and everybody said,"},{"time":676277,"text":"oh, it's okay. We'll get everyone to register their trials, they'll post the protocol,"},{"time":679880,"text":"they'll say what they're going to do before they do it,"},{"time":681904,"text":"and then afterwards we'll be able to check and see if all the trials which"},{"time":684025,"text":"have been conducted and completed have been published."},{"time":686493,"text":"But people didn't bother to use those registers."},{"time":688689,"text":"And so then the International Committee of Medical Journal Editors came along,"},{"time":691308,"text":"and they said, oh, well, we will hold the line."},{"time":692851,"text":"We won't publish any journals, we won't publish any trials,"},{"time":695484,"text":"unless they've been registered before they began."},{"time":698166,"text":"But they didn't hold the line. In 2008, a study was conducted"},{"time":701697,"text":"which showed that half of all of trials published by journals"},{"time":704712,"text":"edited by members of the ICMJE"},{"time":707379,"text":"weren't properly registered, and a quarter of them weren't registered at all."},{"time":712192,"text":"And then finally, the FDA Amendment Act was passed"},{"time":714993,"text":"a couple of years ago saying that everybody who conducts"},{"time":717342,"text":"a trial must post the results of that trial within one year."},{"time":720785,"text":"And in the BMJ, in the first edition of January, 2012,"},{"time":724881,"text":"you can see a study which looks to see if people kept"},{"time":727585,"text":"to that ruling, and it turns out that only one in five"},{"time":731304,"text":"have done so."}]},{"cues":[{"time":734168,"text":"This is a disaster."},{"time":737451,"text":"We cannot know the true effects of the medicines"},{"time":741015,"text":"that we prescribe if we do not have access"},{"time":744231,"text":"to all of the information."}]},{"cues":[{"time":747411,"text":"And this is not a difficult problem to fix."},{"time":751370,"text":"We need to force people to publish all trials"},{"time":756498,"text":"conducted in humans, including the older trials,"},{"time":759469,"text":"because the FDA Amendment Act only asks that you publish the trials conducted after 2008,"},{"time":763414,"text":"and I don't know what world it is in which we're only"},{"time":766027,"text":"practicing medicine on the basis of trials that completed in the past two years."},{"time":770483,"text":"We need to publish all trials in humans,"},{"time":772588,"text":"including the older trials, for all drugs in current use,"},{"time":775662,"text":"and you need to tell everyone you know"},{"time":778578,"text":"that this is a problem and that it has not been fixed."},{"time":782020,"text":"Thank you very much. (Applause)"},{"time":784971,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}